{
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "kernelspec": {
      "name": "maxima",
      "display_name": "Maxima",
      "language": "maxima"
    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Correlation Heatmap\n\nCorrelation measures the linear relationship between pairs of variables.\nThe **Pearson correlation coefficient** $r_{xy}$ ranges from $-1$ (perfect\nanti-correlation) through $0$ (no linear relationship) to $+1$ (perfect\npositive correlation):\n\n$$r_{xy} = \\frac{\\text{cov}(x, y)}{\\sigma_x \\, \\sigma_y}$$\n\nA **correlation matrix** collects all pairwise correlations into one table,\nand a heatmap makes the structure immediately visible. In this notebook we\ngenerate synthetic data with a known correlation structure, compute the\ncorrelation matrix with `np_corrcoef`, and visualize it with `ax_heatmap`.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 1,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Generating Correlated Data\n\nWe build four variables from three independent standard-normal sources\n$z_1, z_2, z_3$.  By constructing linear combinations we control the\ncorrelation structure:\n\n| Variable | Construction | Expected correlations |\n|----------|-------------|----------------------|\n| $x_1$ | $z_1$ | baseline |\n| $x_2$ | $0.8\\,z_1 + 0.6\\,z_2$ | positively correlated with $x_1$ |\n| $x_3$ | $z_3$ | independent of $x_1$ and $x_2$ |\n| $x_4$ | $-0.7\\,z_1 + 0.714\\,z_3$ | anti-correlated with $x_1$ |",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "n : 200$\n\n/* Independent standard-normal sources */\nz1 : np_randn([n])$\nz2 : np_randn([n])$\nz3 : np_randn([n])$\n\n/* Build variables with known correlation structure */\nx1 : z1$\nx2 : np_add(np_scale(0.8, z1), np_scale(0.6, z2))$\nx3 : z3$\nx4 : np_add(np_scale(-0.7, z1), np_scale(0.714, z3))$\n\nprint(\"Generated\", n, \"observations of 4 variables\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 2,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Generated 200 observations of 4 variables"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Stack the four 1D vectors into an n-by-4 matrix (each column is a variable) */\ndata : np_hstack(\n  np_hstack(\n    np_reshape(x1, [n, 1]),\n    np_reshape(x2, [n, 1])\n  ),\n  np_hstack(\n    np_reshape(x3, [n, 1]),\n    np_reshape(x4, [n, 1])\n  )\n)$\nprint(\"Data shape:\", np_shape(data))$\n\n/* Compute the correlation matrix */\nR : np_corrcoef(data)$\nprint(\"Correlation matrix:\")$\nnp_to_matrix(R);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 3,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Data shape: [200,4]\nCorrelation matrix:"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi 1.0&0.8269329360637584&-0.021769619911851976&-0.716420184379767\\cr0.8269329360637584&1.0&-0.053081369397880426&-0.6169110276147319\\cr -0.021769619911851976&-0.053081369397880426&1.0&0.7130999186596808\\cr -0.716420184379767&-0.6169110276147319&0.7130999186596808&1.0\\cr\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 3,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Visualizing the Correlation Matrix\n\nA heatmap with a diverging color scale (red-white-blue) makes positive\nand negative correlations easy to spot at a glance.  The diagonal is\nalways $1$ (each variable is perfectly correlated with itself).",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "ax_draw2d(\n  ax_heatmap(\n    np_to_matrix(R),\n    [\"x1\", \"x2\", \"x3\", \"x4\"],\n    [\"x1\", \"x2\", \"x3\", \"x4\"]\n  ),\n  colorscale=\"RdBu\",\n  title=\"Pearson Correlation Matrix\"\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 4,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "application/x-maxima-plotly": [
              "{\"data\":[{\"x\":[\"x1\",\"x2\",\"x3\",\"x4\"],\"y\":[\"x1\",\"x2\",\"x3\",\"x4\"],\"z\":[[1.0,0.8269329360637584,-0.021769619911851976,-0.716420184379767],[0.8269329360637584,1.0,-0.053081369397880426,-0.6169110276147319],[-0.021769619911851976,-0.053081369397880426,1.0,0.7130999186596808],[-0.716420184379767,-0.6169110276147319,0.7130999186596808,1.0]],\"type\":\"heatmap\",\"name\":\"heatmap\"}],\"layout\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Pearson Correlation Matrix\"},\"width\":700,\"height\":450,\"plot_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"paper_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"xaxis\":{\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1},\"yaxis\":{\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1}}}"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "display_data"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Interpreting Correlations\n\nThe heatmap should show:\n- **x1 vs x2**: strong positive correlation ($r \\approx 0.8$) -- by construction $x_2$ shares $80\\%$ of $z_1$\n- **x1 vs x4**: strong negative correlation ($r \\approx -0.7$) -- $x_4$ has $-0.7\\,z_1$\n- **x1 vs x3**: near zero -- $x_3 = z_3$ is independent of $z_1$\n- **x2 vs x4**: moderate negative correlation -- both share $z_1$ but with opposite signs\n\nLet us verify these relationships with scatter plots of selected pairs.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Most correlated pair: x1 vs x2 */\nax_draw2d(\n  marker_size=4, opacity=0.6,\n  points(x1, x2),\n  title=\"x1 vs x2 (positive correlation)\",\n  xlabel=\"x1\", ylabel=\"x2\",\n  aspect_ratio=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 5,
      "outputs": [
        {
